headline: How a park bench meeting led to Aflac’s $200 million mascot idea
summary: “Quack, quack, Aflac became the idea,” CEO Dan Amos told Fortune. The adoption of the avian mascot has coincided with a 621% run-up in share price.

headline: 1 Large-Cap Stock on Our Buy List and 2 We Ignore
summary: Large-cap stocks usually command their industries because they have the scale to drive market trends. The flip side though is that their sheer size can limit growth as expanding further becomes an increasingly challenging task.
